## 15.2 Resource Extraction

---

### 🔴 513. Oil & Gas Drilling

**What it is:** Drilling wells for crude oil and natural gas exploration and production.

**Players:** ONGC (PSU, big), Reliance (big — KG Basin), Vedanta (big), individual oilfield operators.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 + Contract 📋 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow.

**Challenges:** 💰 Single well costs ₹10Cr-100Cr+ · 📜 DGH/MoPNG regulations · 🧠 Petroleum engineering · 🌊 Oil prices determine viability · 👥 Geopolitical: OPEC, sanctions, energy transition.

**Mistake:** Exploration is gambling with billions. For small players, oilfield SERVICES (drilling support, equipment rental, seismic surveys) is the realistic entry.

**One-liner:** Oil & gas drilling — for small players, enter through services (drilling support, equipment rental), not exploration.

---

### 🔴 514. Natural Gas Processing

**What it is:** Processing raw natural gas — removing impurities (CO2, H2S, water), separating NGLs (Natural Gas Liquids), compressing for pipeline transport.

**Players:** GAIL (PSU, big), Reliance (big), individual gas processing contractors.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 + Contract 📋 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Gas processing plant ₹50Cr-500Cr · 📜 PNGRB regulations · 🧠 Chemical engineering · ⚙ Continuous operation (24/7/365).

**Mistake:** Building without guaranteed gas supply contract. No gas supply = idle plant = losses. Secure long-term gas allocation before construction.

**One-liner:** Process natural gas — secure gas supply contracts before building; idle processing plants burn cash.

---

### 🔴 515. Mineral Processing & Refining

**What it is:** Processing mined ore into usable minerals — crushing, grinding, magnetic separation, flotation, smelting, electrolytic refining.

**Players:** Vedanta (big — multi-mineral), Hindalco (big — alumina refining), NMDC (big), individual mineral processors.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (tolling) + Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Processing plant ₹10Cr-500Cr · 📜 Environmental clearance + CPCB · 🧠 Metallurgical engineering · ⚙ Energy-intensive · 🌊 Commodity price exposure.

**Mistake:** Processing without environmental safeguards. Mineral processing creates tailings (waste) that contain heavy metals. Tailing dam failures (like Brumadinho, Brazil) are catastrophic. Engineer for worst-case scenarios.

**One-liner:** Process minerals — tailing dam safety engineering is as important as the metallurgy; failures are catastrophic.

---

### 🟡 516. Water Well Drilling

**What it is:** Drilling boreholes and tube wells for groundwater — agricultural irrigation, industrial, and domestic water supply.

**Players:** Individual drilling contractors (lakhs), rig manufacturers, state groundwater departments.

**Model:** Service Fee 🔧 (per-foot drilling charge) | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Drilling rig ₹10L-1Cr · 📜 Groundwater extraction increasingly regulated · 🌊 Groundwater depletion is a national crisis · 🧠 Geological knowledge of water-bearing formations · ⚙ Rig maintenance.

**Mistake:** Guaranteeing water when you can't. Groundwater is unpredictable. Charging per-foot-drilled (not per-well-successful) protects you from dry bores.

**One-liner:** Drill water wells — charge per foot drilled, not per successful well; groundwater is unpredictable.

---

### 🟡 517. Timber Harvesting

**What it is:** Legally harvesting timber from plantation forests, farm forestry, or licensed forest areas — for construction, furniture, plywood, paper.

**Players:** State forest departments (regulate), individual timber merchants, ITC (farm forestry initiative).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Forest department transit permit for EVERY log · 📈 India imports 80%+ of timber needs · 🌊 Natural forests are off-limits for commercial logging · 💰 Plantation takes 10-20 years to mature.

**Mistake:** Logging natural forests. It's illegal and carries severe penalties. Only plantation timber and farm forestry timber are legal for commercial harvest.

**One-liner:** Harvest timber — only from plantations and farm forestry; natural forest logging is illegal and carries prison time.

---

### 🔴 518. Peat Extraction

**What it is:** Extracting peat from wetlands — used as growing medium for horticulture, soil amendment, and historically as fuel.

**Players:** Almost no commercial peat extraction in India — very limited deposits. Global: Klasmann-Deilmann, BPB.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow.

**Challenges:** 📜 Wetland protection regulations · 🌊 Environmental concerns (peat bogs are carbon stores) · 📈 Very limited Indian deposits · 👥 Global movement to ban peat extraction for sustainability.

**Mistake:** Investing in peat extraction when global trend is toward banning it. Coco peat (from coconut husks) is the sustainable alternative with growing demand.

**One-liner:** Peat extraction — globally declining; invest in coco peat (coconut husk) instead, which is India's strength.

---

### 🟡 519. Salt Production

**What it is:** Producing salt — solar evaporation of seawater (most common in India), rock salt mining, vacuum evaporation for refined salt.

**Players:** Tata Salt (big), Sambhar Salt (Indian), individual salt works in Gujarat/Rajasthan (thousands), Aashirvaad Salt (ITC).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 💰 Salt pans need large land area near coast · 🌊 Monsoon destroys salt production for 3-4 months · 📈 Commodity pricing — ₹2-5/kg for industrial salt · 📜 Commissioner of Salt regulations.

**Mistake:** Selling only raw industrial salt. Branded, iodized, packaged table salt sells at 10-20x industrial salt price. Tata Salt proved branding works even for salt.

**One-liner:** Produce salt — branded, iodized table salt sells at 10-20x industrial bulk salt; Tata Salt proved branding works.

---

### 🟡 520. Mica Mining

**What it is:** Extracting mica — used in electronics (insulation), cosmetics (shimmer), automotive paints, and construction materials. India produces 25% of global mica.

**Players:** Individual miners in Jharkhand/Bihar/Rajasthan, cosmetic companies (buyers).

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Mining license + environmental clearance · 👥 Child labor concerns in Indian mica mines (major ESG issue) · 🌊 Many mines operate illegally · ⚙ Manual extraction process.

**Mistake:** Sourcing from illegal mines with child labor. Global cosmetic and electronics companies now audit mica supply chains. Non-compliant mica is rejected. Only legal, certified, child-labor-free mica has a market.

**One-liner:** Mine mica — only legal, child-labor-free, certified mica has a market; global buyers audit supply chains.

---

### 🔴 521. Graphite Mining

**What it is:** Extracting graphite — used in batteries (anode material for Li-ion), lubricants, refractories, and pencils. India has significant deposits.

**Players:** HEG (Indian, big — graphite electrodes), Tirupati Graphite (Indian, medium), individual miners.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🐢 Slow.

**Challenges:** 📜 Mining lease + environmental clearance · 💰 Processing (spheronization for batteries) is expensive · 👥 Graphite is a critical mineral for EV batteries · 🌊 China dominates graphite processing.

**Mistake:** Selling raw flake graphite. The value is in PROCESSED graphite — spherical graphite for battery anodes sells at 10-20x raw flake.

**One-liner:** Mine graphite — process into battery-grade spherical graphite for 10-20x raw flake value; EV demand is exploding.

---

### 🟡 522. Silica Sand Extraction

**What it is:** Mining high-purity silica (quartz) sand — used for glass manufacturing, foundry casting, silicon wafers, water filtration.

**Players:** Individual silica sand miners, glass companies (buyers), foundries.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Mining lease + environmental clearance · 📈 Purity determines price (99.5%+ SiO2 for solar/semiconductor grade) · ⚙ Washing and grading infrastructure · 💰 Transport (sand is heavy).

**Mistake:** Selling ungraded mixed silica. Properly washed, graded, and purity-tested silica commands 5-10x ungraded prices. Quality testing capability is the differentiator.

**One-liner:** Extract silica sand — washing, grading, and purity testing multiply value 5-10x over selling unprocessed.

