## 16.1 Government Supply

---

### 🟢 523. Office Supplies to Government

**What it is:** Selling stationery, paper, printers, cartridges, and office consumables to government offices through GeM (Government e-Marketplace).

**Players:** Any GST-registered business on GeM. Thousands of small suppliers.

**Model:** Product Sale 📦 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 GeM registration required · 📈 L1 (lowest price) wins most bids · 🕐 Payment 30-90 days · ⚙ Strict delivery timelines · 💰 Thin margins on commodity items.

**Mistake:** Bidding unrealistically low just to win. Loss-making contracts lead to poor quality delivery → blacklisting. Price realistically.

**One-liner:** Sell office supplies to government on GeM — bid realistically; blacklisting for poor delivery is worse than losing a bid.

---

### 🟡 524. Uniform & Textile Supply

**What it is:** Supplying uniforms to government employees, police, military, schools, hospitals — through government tenders.

**Players:** Individual uniform manufacturers, ordnance factories (military), state procurement agencies.

**Model:** Contract 📋 | **Revenue:** 🔄 Medium.

**Challenges:** 📜 Tender specifications are extremely detailed · ⚙ Quality inspection by government officials · 💰 Large volume orders need working capital · 🕐 Payment cycles 60-120 days.

**Mistake:** Not reading tender specifications carefully. One deviation (wrong thread count, wrong color shade, wrong button) = rejected lot = financial loss.

**One-liner:** Supply government uniforms — read every tender specification word-by-word; one deviation means total lot rejection.

